## Create AWS Secret File

* Create a file named:

``` 
aws-secret.yaml
```

* Add the below content and update your AWS credentials:

```
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: aws-secret
  namespace: portfolio

type: Opaque

stringData:
  AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID: "<paste-access-key>"
  AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: "<paste-secret-access-key>"
```

## Apply AWS Secret

* Run:

```
kubectl apply -f aws-secret.yaml
```

## Export AWS Credentials

* Run:

```bash 
export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<paste-access-key>

export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<paste-secret-access-key>

export AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1
```

## Create ECR Docker Secret

* Run:

```bash 
kubectl create secret docker-registry ecr-secret \
  --docker-server=443628962956.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com \
  --docker-username=AWS \
  --docker-password=$(aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1) \
  --namespace=portfolio
```

## Verify Secret

* Run:

```bash 
kubectl get secrets -n portfolio
```

* You should see:

```text 
ecr-secret   kubernetes.io/dockerconfigjson
```
